function [OutMatrix] = changecon(InMatrix,size,amount,type)% function [OutMatrix] = Change_Contrast(InMatrix,size,amount,type)%% Changes the contrast energy of a square matrix INMATRIX of size SIZExSIZE% by a given AMOUNT. TYPE specifies what kind of change AMOUNT is. If TYPE % is 'relative' the image's contrast is changed by AMOUNT times the original.% If TYPE is 'absolute' the image's contrast variance is set to AMOUNT. The default% is 'absolute'. The result is returned in OUTMATRIX. % Change_Contrast requires Lum2Con, Con2Lum, and Change_Variance.%% June 22, 1996		J Gold	P J Bennett A B Sekuler 	University of Toronto Vision Lab   [ConMatrix,Lave] = Lum2Con(InMatrix,size);NewConMatrix = Change_Variance(ConMatrix,size,amount,type);OutMatrix = Con2Lum(NewConMatrix,Lave);return